  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And he brought forth the king's son,.... Out of the apartment in the temple where he had been brought up: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and put the crown upon him; the crown royal, which seems to have been kept in the temple: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and gave him the testimony; the book of the law, which he was to read in all his days, and according to it govern the people; and which was a testimony of the will of God both to him and them: Kimchi and Ben Melech interpret it of royal garments put upon him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they made him king, and anointed him; proclaimed and declared him king, and anointed him, for the confirmation of it, because of the pretension Athaliah made to the kingdom; otherwise, as the Jewish writers say, the son of a king was not anointed; and hence, they say, it was, that Solomon was anointed, because of the claim of Adonijah: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they clapped their hands; in token of joy: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and said, God save the king; or, \"let the king live\"; or, \"may he prosper\", as the Targum; may health and prosperity attend him in his government. In 2 Chronicles 23:11, it is said; \"Jehoiada and his sons anointed him\", and said those words; among whom must be Zechariah, whom this king afterwards slew, which was an instance of great ingratitude, 2 Chronicles 24:20. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and said, God save the king; or, \"let the king live\"; or, \"may he prosper\", as the Targum; may health and prosperity attend him in his government. In ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 23:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", it is said; \"Jehoiada and his sons anointed him\", and said those words; among whom must be Zechariah, whom this king afterwards slew, which was an instance of great ingratitude, ",
            "children": []
